org.typemeta.funcj.data

Interface Lazy<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of value
    All Superinterfaces:
    Functions.F0<T>

    public interface Lazy<T>
extends Functions.F0<T>
    Wrapper for values which are computed lazily, i.e. on demand. The result is computed once and cached.

    • Method Detail

      • of

        static <T> Lazy<T> of(Functions.F0<T> get)
        Construct a lazy value from a value supplier. The lazy value is not thread-safe, meaning the supplier may be invoked multiple times if the Lazy value is passed to multiple threads before it is computed.
        Type Parameters:
        T - value type
        Parameters:
        get - supplier of the value
        Returns:
        lazy value

      • ofTS

        static <T> Lazy<T> ofTS(Functions.F0<T> get)
        Construct a lazy value from a value supplier. The lazy value is thread-safe, meaning the supplier will only be invoked once, even if the Lazy value is passed to multiple threads.
        Type Parameters:
        T - value type
        Parameters:
        get - supplier of the value
        Returns:
        lazy value
